-- This script is just for drawing the starfield background and can be removed if desired. All game logic is in the other script. -- Enjoy! -- -Jon
stars = {} w = 288 h = 160 cx = w / 2 cy = h / 2
function onTick() while #stars < 200 do addStar(math.random(0, w), math.random(0, h)) end
if input.getBool(1) then for i=1, #stars do stars[i].depth = math.min(1, stars[i].depth + stars[i].speed) stars[i].x = stars[i].x + stars[i].vx * stars[i].depth stars[i].y = stars[i].y + stars[i].vy * stars[i].depth
if stars[i].x < 0 or stars[i].x > w or stars[i].y < 0 or stars[i].y > h then resetStar(math.random(0, w), math.random(0, h), stars[i]) end end end end
function addStar(x, y) star = {} stars[#stars+1] = star resetStar(x,y,star) star.depth = math.random() end
function resetStar(x,y,star) star.x = x star.y = y star.depth = 0 offset_x = star.x - cx offset_y = star.y - cy dist = math.sqrt(offset_x*offset_x+offset_y*offset_y) star.vx = offset_x / dist star.vy = offset_y / dist star.speed = 0.001 + math.random() * 0.009 end
function onDraw() screen.setColor(0, 0, 0) screen.drawClear()
for i=1, #stars do val = stars[i].depth * 255 screen.setColor(val, val, val, val) screen.drawLine(stars[i].x, stars[i].y, stars[i].x+1, stars[i].y+1) end end
